@NODE "introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"

                              Introduction

 A  number  of people were asking me for a program, that allows to edit
 HTML  files  with coloured HTML  tags  etc.   I  have tried to connect
 TextEditor  and  HTMLtext  MUI  custom  classes  together.  Well...  I
 succeeded (I think) and so here You have an HTML editor.

 This editor is both WYSIWYG and text editor.  You edit Your webpage as
 a text (like in CED) but You can immediatly see it in HTMLtext display
 object.

 NOTE that  HTMLtext.mcc gadget in this version doesn't support frames,
 forms nad few other things.  Don't be suprised when they won't come up
 in  HTML  text  gadget.   But You can connect external HTML browser to
 this  editor  (by ARexx) and make internal HTML text gadget invisible.
 There  is  an  example  ARexx script in rexx directory in this archive
 witch loads edited file to AWeb.

Features:

 + Runs on the best computer ever made - Amiga.
 + Fully AmigaOS friendly.
 + Fully Localized.
 + Uses MUI.
 + ARexx port and over 30 ARexx commands.
 + Coloured HTML tags.
 + Easy creation of frames, tables, lists etc.
 + Both WYSIWYG and text editor.
 + Keeps its program and data in its home directory - no files has to
   be put in other dirs.
 + Automatic conversion AmigaPL <-> ISO-8859-2 (for Poles).

 This program, or it's parts were tested on:

 A1200 3.1 020EC/14 6Mb
 A1200 3.1 060/50 & 603e+/240 34Mb
 A1200 3.0 040/40 34Mb
 A4000 3.1 060/66 & 604e/233 38Mb

@ENDNODE

@NODE "requirements" "Requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"

This program requires to run:

 + An Amiga computer or compatibile (I dont know if it'll run on DRACO)
 + OS 3.0 or better.
 + CPU MC68020EC or better.
 + @{"MUI" LINK "MUI"} installed to Your system.
 + @{"TextEditor.mcc" LINK "texteditor"} installed.

Recomended:

 + @{"HTMLtext.mcc" LINK "htmltext"} installed.
 + Hard drive.
 + More memory, CPU etc..
@ENDNODE

@NODE "distribution" "Dristribution"
@TOC "MAIN"

                              Distribution

    The  unegistered  version of this program may be freely distributed
 in  any  kind  of  data  storage.   It  can be freely placed on Aminet
 (including  Aminet  CD's),  Cover  CD's (WITHOUT sending a copy to the
 author), PD disk collections etc.  You can't take a money from selling
 it except a normal fee for copying disks of a price of producing CD.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Shareware" "Shareware"
@TOC "MAIN"

                           Shareware product

   This  program is a Shareware.  It means that you can use it for free
 but  if  You  think  It  is worth using and supporting then You should
 register.    Registration  costs  only  US$  3  or 10  PLN.   See  the
 @{"registration" LINK "register"}  part  to  know what are advantages of being a registered
 user.

   There  is  also  one  thing:  This  program  may  not be used to any
 military  purpose.  You can't use it to create webpages that describes
 anything related to army.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "instalation" "How to install"
@TOC "MAIN"

                              Instalation
   There  is  an  installer  script  witch  just  copies  all files to
 selected  directory.   That's  all  instalation  so  You  may  do  it
 manually if You want.

   To install HTML editor just copy it somewhere to Your hard drive (or
 a  disk  if You want).  There are no assigns or other things needed to
 run  it.   Note  that  You dont have to copy contents of the catalogs/
 directory  to Your Locale:catalogs/ dir because this program looks for
 other  translation first in it's progdir:catalogs/ dir and after it in
 Locate:catalogs/.  This can prevent You from mess on Your HD and allow
 easy deletion this program  - just delete its directory and You'll get
 rid  of  it.  The only thing left will be MUI custom classes installed
 in  MUI:libs/mui/ but I suggest to leave them because they can be used
 in  other  MUI applications too.  They are not included in archive and
 they are not mine so I cant decide about their installation.

   Note  also  that  such  locale  access  (first  in home dir, next in
 Locale:catalogs/)  is  done by AmigaOS so it's true for other programs
 too.

   Also   note  that  configuration  files  (witch  are  saved  in  the
 ENVARC:mui/HTMLEDIT.1.cfg   file)  are  exchangeable  in  versions  of
 HTMLEditor.   You  can  use  old  configuration to new version of this
 proggy.   All  settings  that  were in previous version will be set to
 Your  preffered  settings.  New settings, that appeared in new version
 of  HTMLEdit will be set to default.  Saving configuration is the only
 thing  when  something  is  written not in programs home directory but
 ENVARC:mui/  dir  is  done by MUI and it is suggested by the author of
 MUI so I follow the rules of MUI programming.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "contents" "Contents of this archive"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Contents of this archive:

 + HTMLEditor - main program
 + HTML-tags - file containing tags definitions for "insert" menu
 + Install - installer script
 + docs/ - here You'll find the documentation.
 + rexx/ - here are some ARexx scripts.
 + catalogs/ - here You'll find few translations for this proggy.

 No file can be added or remooved from the archive without permission
 from the author.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gadgets" "Gadgets"
@TOC "MAIN"

  In  the  program's window You can see a number of gadgets.  There are
 two  big  gadgets:   TextEditor gadget - where You can write Your text
 and  HTML  gadget  where  You can see how it will look like.  There is
 also  an toolbar containing a number of image gadgets that should help
 while work on Your webpage.  Note that if You leave Your mouse pointer
 over  such  a  gadget  for a while You'll see a bubble help saying the
 meaning of this gadget.  The gadgets are:

      @{"  Refresh           " LINK "gad_refresh"}
      @{"  Cut               " LINK "gad_cut"}
      @{"  Copy              " LINK "gad_copy"}
      @{"  Paste             " LINK "gad_paste"}
      @{"  Erase             " LINK "gad_erase"}
      @{"  Undo              " LINK "gad_undo"}
      @{"  Redo              " LINK "gad_redo"}

      @{"  Bold              " LINK "gad_bold"}
      @{"  Italics           " LINK "gad_bold"}
      @{"  Underlined        " LINK "gad_bold"}

      @{"  Left              " LINK "gad_left"}
      @{"  Center            " LINK "gad_left"}
      @{"  Right             " LINK "gad_left"}

      @{"  H1 ... H6         " LINK "gad_h1"}

      @{"  BR                " LINK "gad_br"}
      @{"  Paragraph         " LINK "gad_paragraph"}
      @{"  Comment           " LINK "gad_comment"}
      @{"  Superscript       " LINK "gad_sup"}
      @{"  Subscript         " LINK "gad_sup"}

      @{"  Create List...    " LINK "gad_clist"}
      @{"  Create Table...   " LINK "gad_ctable"}
      @{"  Create Frame...   " LINK "gad_cframe"}
      @{"  Create E-mail...  " LINK "gad_cmail"}
      @{"  Create Link...    " LINK "gad_clink"}
      @{"  Create Image...   " LINK "gad_cimage"}
      @{"  Create HR...      " LINK "gad_chr"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_refresh" "Refresh"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Refresh:

      Refreshes  the  contents  of  HTML  text gadget according to
      contents of a texteditor gadget
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_cut" "Cut"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Cut:

      Copies   marked  text  to  clipboard  and  removes  it  from
      TextEditor gadget.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_copy" "Copy"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Copy:

      Just copies marked text to clipboard.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_paste" "Paste"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Paste:

      Inserts text from clipboard to the TextEditor gadget
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_erase" "Erase"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Erase:

      Erases marked text without copying it to clipboard.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_undo" "Undo"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Undo:

      Undo last operation.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_redo" "Redo"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Redo:

      Redo last undo.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_bold" "Bold, Italics, Underlined"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Bold, Italics, Underlined:

      Makes  marked  text  bold,  italics  or  underlined or justs
      inserts HTML tags for this if there is no marked text.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_left" "Left, Center, Right"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Left, Center, Right:

      If  there is marked text, makes an paragraph of it justified
      left,  center  or  right.  If  nothing  is  marked then just
      inserts such a HTML tags at the cursor position.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_h1" "H1 - H6"
@TOC "MAIN"

  H1 ... H6:

      Makes  marked  text  to  be header1...6 or just inserts HTML
      tags for this if nothing is marked.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_br" "BR"
@TOC "MAIN"

  BR

      Insterts <BR> tag.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_paragraph" "Paragraph"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Paragraph

      Inserts  <P></P>  tags to create new paragraph.  If there is
      marked text then it makes an paragraph of it.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_comment" "Comment"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Comment

      Makes a comment from marked text.  If nothing is marked then
      just inserts comment tags at the cursor position.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_sup" "Superscript, Subscript"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Superscript, Subscript:

      Makes  marked  text  a  superscript  or  subscript text.  If
      nothing  is  marked  then just inserts superscript/subscript
      tags.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_clist" "Create List..."
@TOC "MAIN"

  Create List...

      This  gadget  pops up an requester where You can set various
      attributes  of  list.   After setting the number of elements
      and  type  You can press "Create" and the blank list will be
      created.  If You have marked some text then there will be an
      "From  Text" gadget in requester available.  If You press it
      then  marked  text will be turned to list of specified type.
      Each  line  of  text  will  be one list entry.  In this case
      value  set  in "Nuber of elements" is ignored.  Note that if
      You  want  to  create list from text, there must be at least
      one line more below the text.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_ctable" "Create Table..."
@TOC "MAIN"

  Create Table...

      This  pops  up  the  requester  to create table.  As for now
      there  are only basic attributes of table in this requester.
      More attributes will be added in next version.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_cframe" "Create Frame..."
@TOC "MAIN"

  Create Frame...

      This pops up an requester to create frames.  You can set the
      layout  and  the  number of frames.  All created frames have
      the  same  size  - You can change it manulally in <FRAMESET>
      attributes where You'll see the sizes of all frames.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_cmail" "Create Email..."
@TOC "MAIN"

  Create Email...

      This pops up an requester to create an mailto link.  You can
      create  it  from  marked  text  or  from  contents of string
      gadgets.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_clink" "Create Link..."
@TOC "MAIN"

  Create Link...

      This  pops  up  an  requester  to create link.  Just like in
      e-mail creation You can set the name and address of an link.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_cimage" "Create Image..."
@TOC "MAIN"

  Create Image...

      This  creates  an image.  You can choose an image address or
      type  it  and  type  the  text, that is to be displayed when
      image  is  unavailable.   You  can  aslo specify here border
      width, spacings, sizes and align of an image
@ENDNODE

@NODE "gad_chr" "Create Horizontal Line..."
@TOC "MAIN"

  Create Horizontal Line...

      This  creates  an  horizontal  separator  line.  You can set
      align  (left,  centered  or  right),  width of separator (in
      percents), its height in pixels and turn on/off the shade in
      it.   Note that if You wont change anything in requester and
      just  press  "create" then it'll insert just a simple "<HR>"
      tag.
@ENDNODE

