@NODE "men_new" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  New:

      In  pre  1.31 versions it just cleared contents of text edit
      gadget  and  put some kind of blank HTML page there.  Now it
      opens  a  requester where You can specify various attributes
      of HTML file.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_clear" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Clear:

      Clears contents of TextEditor gadget.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_load" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Load...:

      Loads a file using asl requester.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_save" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Save...:

      Saves a file
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_about" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  About...:

      Displays info about this program.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_exit" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Exit:

      Quits the program.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_refresh" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Refresh:

      Refreshes  the  contents  of  the  HTML display according to
      current contents of TextEditor gadget.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_refreshtext" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Refresh Text:

      Refreshes  the  contents  of TextEditor gadget.  If You have
      typed some HTML tags manually then this will make them to be
      displayed  in  correct  colour.   This is also a good way to
      check  if  there are no basic errors in HTML file because if
      You  wont,  for example, close an HTML tag using '>' colours
      will  be  wrong  displayed  and  You'll  be  able to see it.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_cutcopypaste" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Cut, Copy, Paste, Erase, Undo, Redo:

      These  menu  items  has  the same actions as gadgets in edit
      toolbar.  There are no hotkeys in menu because they are user
      configurable  in MUI-TextEditor settings.  Read the settings
      of  TextEditor in MUI settings window and You'll know how to
      reach it from keyboard.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_insert" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Insert:

      Inserts  an  HTML  tag  in  the  current cursor position and
      refreshes contents of HTML display.

      The  tags  are  defined  in file "HTML-tags" witch should be
      found in the same directory, where the main program is.  You
      can  freely  change  the contenst of this file and put there
      HTML  tags witch You use most.  Each menu item witch inserts
      the  HTML  tag  is  defined by four lines in this text file.
      First  line  is  a  name,  witch  should appear in the menu.
      Second  line is a char that will appear as a key shortcut in
      menu.   If  You  specify a longer string here then the first
      character  will  be  treated  as a key shortcut char.  Third
      line  is  a  text that is to be inserted at the beginning of
      marked  text  and foutrh line is a text to insert at the end
      of  marked  text.  If there is no marked text then both tags
      will be inserted at the cursor position.  So for example:

      .
      .
      Bold
      B
      <b>
      </b>
      .
      .

      Will  make  marked text bold or just insert "<b></b>" at the
      cursor  position  if  tere is no marked text.  The menu item
      will  look  like:  "Bold B".  If You want to insert just one
      tag  like  <hr>  then just specify first text to be inserted
      and a empty line as the second text.

      I  did  it  like  this  because  I  was to lazy to implement
      manually  all important tags.  In archive You should find an
      example file with few frequently used HTML tags.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_create" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

Create:

      Here  are  built  in requesters that helps to create various
      HTML  tags.   For more detailed description of these see the
      gadgets description.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_convert" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  AmigaPL <-> ISO:

      If checked causes program to automaticly convert loaded file
      from  ISO  to  AmigaPL.   While saving It converts file from
      AmigaPL  to ISO.  This is useless if You dont want to create
      WWW in polish language but it is extremely useful for poles.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_arefresh" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  AutoRefresh:

      If  checked causes program to refresh contents of HTML gadget
      after each inserting of HTML tag.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_show" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Show:

      This  menu  item  causes  various GUI elements to appear and
      disappear.   The  subitems allows to choose witch one should
      be displayed.  Subitems are:

      Edit Toolbar:

      Here You can turn on and off the edit toolbar.

      Info text gadget:

      This  causes  the  textgadget  on  the top  of the window to
      appear and disappear.  this gadget is rather useless because
      it  only  says "HTMLEditor copyright..." and does nothing so
      if  You  dont  like space consuming GUI elements then You'll
      perhaps  want  to  hide  it.   Note that this option is only
      available if You have registered HTMLEditor.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_txtscroll" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Text Scrollbar:

      Here  You  can  specify  where  the  text scroller should be
      displayed.  You can turn it off (by selecting 'none'), place
      it on left or right side of text editor gadget.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_htmltxt" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  HTML Text:

      This menu item lets You to turn on and off HTML text gadget.
      You can turn it off (by selecting 'none').  You can place it
      inside  of  programs  window (like it was placed in pre 1.31
      versions).  At least You can also put it in separate window.

      Note  that  You  can't  change  this  directly from separate
      window  to  programs window etc.  If the HTML text gadget is
      displayed  in  one  of  the  positions  You  can change it's
      position  only  by  selecting 'none' first and then and then
      selecting  another  position.  If You'll activate one of 'in
      editor  window'  or  'in separate window' You'll notice that
      the  other  option will get disabled.  This is done that way
      because   I  had  problems  while  switching  the  positions
      directly.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_tagcolor" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  HTML tags colours:

      There  are  four menu items where You can select colours for
      different  parts  of HTML text.  First You can select colour
      of  normal text (but this option does'nt work very good with
      current  version  of TextEditor.mcc).  Next is the colour of
      HTML  tags - in fact this does'nt check if the tag is really
      HTML tags but marks everything between '<' and '>' brackets.
      Third  is  the colour of attributes inside of HTML tags.  If
      You  have  for  example <P align="left"> tag then the 'left'
      word  will  be drawn in this colour.  the last is the colour
      for  HTML  comments  -  everything  beetween  '<!'  and  '>'
      brackets.

      You  can  select  here  one of MUI's predefined colours.  In
      next version I'll creare an requester here so You'll be able
      to  really  choose  a  colour You want (just like You choose
      colours in MUI preferences).
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_colortags" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

   Coloured HTML tags:

      This  menu  item enables to turn on/off colour HTML tags. If
      You  turn  it  off  then whole text (including tags) will be
      displayed  in  one colour. This may seem sensless but colour
      tags  was making trouble sometimes and it seems to be an bug
      in  TextEditor.mcc.   So  I added option allowing to disable
      it.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_savecfg" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  Save:

      Saves  the  current  settings to disk.  The settings will be
      loaded  at every  start of the program.  This option is only
      available if You have registered HTMLEditor.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "men_muicfg" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

  MUI:

      This  runs  MUI  settings  for  this  application.  If You'll
      change  these settings and save it, new settings will be used
      only for this program.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "arexx" "ARexx commands"
@TOC "MAIN"

                             ARexx commands

  Since  v  1.2  HTML Editor has an ARexx port and supports a number of
 commands.   There are general MUI commands - they are supported by all
 MUI  applications  and  in  fact, they were also supported by previous
 versions of HTML Editor.  There are TextEditor commands witch operates
 on text inside of TextEditor gadget.  There are also 'custom' commands
 witch are unique for HTML Editor program.

  Note that in rexx dir there is an example ARexx script to show how to
 use  these commands.  There is also an example how to load edited file
 to AWeb by using ARexx.

  For MUI  commands see documentation of MUI - there they are explained
 so I don't see sense to describe them twice.

TextEditor commands:
====================

  These  are commands supported by the TextEditor gadget.  So if You'll
 find  other application that uses TextEditor.mcc and has an ARexx port
 then  it  will  porbably  support  the  same  commands.  Some of these
 commands  has  special  arguments.  The list below is just a copy from
 the  TextEditor.mcc  autodocs.   If  You're really interested in ARexx
 then  I sugest to refer to TextEditor.mcc docs for it's ARexx commands
 because You might have newer wersion of this gadget on Your system and
 There can be more ARexx commands supported by it.

  CUT
  COPY
  PASTE
  ERASE
  UNDO
  REDO
  CLEAR
  GOTOLINE        /N/A
  GOTOCOLUMN      /N/A
  CURSOR          Up/S,Down/S,Left/S,Right/S
  LINE            /N/A
  COLUMN          /N/A
  NEXT            Word/S,Sentence/S,Paragraph/S,Page/S
  PREVIOUS        Word/S,Sentence/S,Paragraph/S,Page/S
  POSITION        SOF/S,EOF/S,SOL/S,EOL/S,SOW/S,EOW/S,SOV/S,EOV/S
  SETBOOKMARK     /N/A
  GOTOBOOKMARK    /N/A
  TEXT            /F
  GETLINE
  GETCURSOR       Line/S,Column/S
  MARK            On/S,Off/S
  DELETE
  BACKSPACE


HTMLEditor commands:
====================

  These  are  commands  that  are unique for HTML Editor - You wont see
 them in any other application.

  NEWFILE
  SAVEFILE
  LOADFILE
  REFRESH

  These  commands  are similar to menu items with the same names.  They
 support no arguments.  As for SAVEFILE and LOADFILE they just bring up
 well known file requester to let the user choose a file.

  INSERT         START/A,END

  This  is  similar to 'insert' menu item.  As an arguments You specify
 the  text,  that  is to be inserted at the beggining and at the end of
 marked  area.   If You just want to insert some text then specify only
 the first argument.

  LOAD           NAME/A
  SAVE           NAME/A

  These two commands loads and saves file from/to disk.  As an argument
 You should specify name of s file to be loaded.  By using save command
 You  can  simply  connect this editor to some HTML browser - just save
 the  file somewhere to disk or ramdisk or a pipe device :) and load it
 to Your favourite browser.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "news" "What's new in v 1.31"
@TOC "MAIN"

What's new in v 1.31?

+ Selecting "NEW" no longer inserts some kind of blank HTML page.
  Instead it opens an requester where You can specify various attributes
  of HTML file.
+ Added HR creation button and menu item.
+ All of the "create" requesters has now key shortcuts to all of their
  gadgets.
+ New options in "Create image" requester.
+ Now text has more colours. different colours are for text, HTML tags,
  HTML tag arrtibutes (in "") and comments.
+ An "about" arexx command remooved - it was useless.
+ The code was modified. Lots of small improovements that are not
  visible for user but makes code work better.
+ File requester for loading/saving files has now normal size. It's
  position and width are default for ASL and height is the same as
  height of program window.
+ Added "refresh text" option for refreshing the colours of text.
+ Installer script added.
+ Localizations are now in separate archives. They should be laying
  somwhere near the main archive on the place, from where You
  downloaded it. Only Polish locale come with the archive.
+ You can now have a HTML text gadget displayed in separate window, not
  only in program's main window.
+ at least program checks if the file has been saved when You selected
  load new file, clear the editor or exit and asks You do You want to
  save it.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "MUI" "Magic User Interface"
@TOC "MAIN"

This application uses:


                        MUI - MagicUserInterface

                (c) Copyright 1992-97 by Stefan Stuntz


MUI is a system to generate and maintain graphical user interfaces. With
the  aid  of  a  preferences program, the user of an application has the
ability to customize the outfit according to his personal taste.

MUI is distributed as shareware. To obtain a complete package containing
lots of examples and more information about registration please look for
a  file  called  "muiXXusr.lha"  (XX means the latest version number) on
your local bulletin boards or on public domain disks.

          If you want to register directly, feel free to send


                         DM 30.-  or  US$ 20.-

