@NODE "history" "History"
@TOC "MAIN"

1.31

 see @{"What's new?" LINK "news"}

1.3 (20.06.98)

 + Now program's window is an appwindow - You can drop icons on it and
   their files will be loaded.
 + Some minor bugs fixed.
 + A creation of lists, frames, images, links and tables was added.
 + Now this proggy can run without an HTMLtext.mcc. If it is not
   available then HTML text gadget wont appear but the program will
   work fine.
 + Now edit gadgets has images instead of texts inside of them. There
   are also many new gadgets that should help with creating HTML
   document.
 + Added show info text option.
 + German translation added.
 + Swedish translation added.

1.21 (25.05.98)

 + Saving file by Arexx will no longer cause requester to try open
   in directory where the Arexx saved file is. For exampel if You'll
   save file by Arexx to "PIPE:my_file.html" and You'll now try to
   open save or load requester it wont try to open in PIPE: device.
 + Added "Clear" menu item.
 + Added HTML tags colour option.
 + Added french catalog file done by Didier Giron - thanks !
 + Now Load/Save file requesters are opened not somewhere on screen
   but over the program window.

1.2 (21.05.98)

 + Added ARexx interface and many ARexx commands
 + Few localization corrections.
 + Added Show HTML text option
 + Added scrollbar for TextEditor gadget and a Text Scrollbar option
 + I have mooved HTMLtext scrollers from window border to the neighbour
   of HTMLtext object so they could disappear with this object. Some
   users were confused when they mooved scroller of the window and only
   one gadget in it was reacting on it.
 + Now "insert" menu item gets disabled if there is no "HTML-tags" file.
 + Added Show Edit tools option
 + There was a bug in AmigaPL <-> ISO conversion. Some chars were
   converted to wrong chars of other charset. Now it works correctly
 + There were problems if there were images in edited HTML file. The
   HTML display gadget didn't displayed them if they were not in
   porgrams directory. Now it works good

1.1 (15.05.98)

 + Now You can mark text, select edit/insert/bold for example and
   program will insert <b> and </b> tags at the both sides of marked
   text.
 + I have added few Bubble helps to make it more user friendly.
 + I have localized the program. In the archive there is a catalog
   file with polish translations.
 + I have added Auto Refresh option (see usage)

1.0 (14.05.98)

 First public release
@ENDNODE


@NODE "future" "Future plans"
@TOC "MAIN"

                              Future plans

   Well...  Nobody  knows  the  future  but  I  have some ideas of this
 program.   Things,  that  I  would like to implement in future are (in
 random order):

 + More ARexx commands
 + Edition of many files at one time.
 + An requester for easy creation of forms - Whole form will be created
   by one requester!
 + An some kind of requester - gfx editor that would help while creating
   maps. This would be rather complex and I dont know when I'll do it.
 + Ability to run Dos command/ARexx script from a menu or button. This
   would enable to create button that puts currently edited page to
   external HTML browser (via ARexx)
 + Printing the source of HTML file with highlighted HTML tags.
 + Some kind of checking the file to detect errors.
 + Many user configurable things.
 + More user configurable things.
 + A lot more user configurable things.
 + .. and many many more.

  If  You  have  any  comments or ideas about what else would be useful
 then write to @{"me" LINK "author"}.

  If  You  want  to  translate this proggy to Your language then please
 also  write  to me.  I expect You have already translated few programs
 before.

  I don't know why but althrougth I implement new features in every new
 version  of  HTML  Editor,  in  every version this list doesn't become
 smaller but grows up and up ;)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "bugs" "Bugs"
@TOC "MAIN"

   Unfortunately this chapter has been born.  That is because few users
 has reported me about system crashes.

 -  HTML text MUI custom class is a little buggy.  So I recomend to use
 external browser instead of internal HTMLtext gadget.  In this version
 when  You  turn  off  the  HTMLtext  gadget  it  wont  be loaded so it
 should'nt make any trouble.

 -  There  seems  to  be an bug in TextEditor MUI custom class.  It can
 crash  Your  system  if  there are many colours in text. Few users has
 reported  that  HTMLEditor  crashes  sometimes while inserting tags or
 while  starting  new  HTML document. I think this is caused by colours
 used  in  HTML tags. I have reported this to TextEditor.mcc author and
 he  promised to check it.  Check the version of TextEditor.mcc on Your
 hard drive.  If its later than 15.4 then probably this was fixed.

 - I sometimes had trouble while creating a list of text.  The list was
 created not from text.  I think I have solved the problem but I You'll
 have problems with it please report me.

 - This program often crashes if  there is  pc2amiga program active.  I
 dont know the reason and I can't find a bug in my proggy.

 If  You find a bug, Your system crashes while work of this proggy then
 please  write  to  me  about it.  But first make sure it's a bug in my
 editor  - disable the HTMLtext gadget and colour HTML tags. If the bug
 will still be up - write to me and describe it in details.
@ENDNODE

